  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed takeaway use, by reason of noise and disturbance caused by customers entering and leaving the premises, vehicles parking and manoeuvring, particularly during the evening hours of operation, would be detrimental to the amenities of the occupiers of nearby residential properties, contrary to Havering Development Control Policies DC32, DC36, DC55, DC61 and DC63, Havering Draft Local Plan Policies 7, 26 and 34, and London Plan (2021) policies D14 and T6.",
    "The proposal would introduce an incompatible use in a location designated for residential development prejudicing the delivery of high quality residential development within the wider Rainham and Beam Park Strategic Development Area and would also result in the net loss of residential floorspace on the site contrary to policies DC1 and DC61 of the Havering Core Strategy and Development Control Policies Development Plan Document (2008), Draft Local Plan policies 2 and 3 and London Plan policies D3 and SD10.",
    "Statement Required by Article 35 (2) of the Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015: Consideration was given to seeking amendments, but given conflict with adopted planning policy, notification of intended refusal and the reason(s) for it was given in writing to the Agent on the 08/09/21."
  ],
